post.description:
Authenticate a user and return access and refresh tokens.

You can authenticate using either:
1. Form data (x-www-form-urlencoded):
   - username: User's email address
   - password: User's password

2. JSON (application/json):
   {
     "email": "user@example.com",
     "password": "yourpassword"
   }

Returns:
{
  "access_token": "jwt.token.here",
  "token_type": "bearer",
  "user": {
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "role": "user",
    "is_active": true
  }
}

📥 Handles M-PESA B2C Result Callback (Success or Failure)

This route is called by Safaricom once a B2C payment request has been processed.
It contains the result of the transaction — whether it was successful or failed.

The endpoint parses and normalizes the callback into a `B2CCallbackSchema`, then
delegates processing to downstream logic.

Docs:
    https://developer.safaricom.co.ke/APIs/M-PESA-B2C

Sample Payload:
{
    "Result": {
        "ResultType": 0,
        "ResultCode": 0,
        "ResultDesc": "The service request is processed successfully.",
        "OriginatorConversationID": "FILE123",
        "ConversationID": "AG_20250510_XXXX",
        "TransactionID": "TX123456",
        "ResultParameters": {
            "ResultParameter": [
                {"Key": "TransactionAmount", "Value": 100},
                {"Key": "TransactionReceipt", "Value": "TX123456"},
                ...
            ]
        },
        "ReferenceData": {
            "ReferenceItem": {
                "Key": "QueueTimeoutURL",
                "Value": "https://internal.safaricom.co.ke/b2cresults/v1/submit"
            }
        }
    }
}

Returns:
    dict: Acknowledgment of receipt (used by Safaricom to stop retries).

get.description:
Retrieve KPI values for the transactions page overview cards with status and order type breakdown.

Priority:
1. If start_date and/or end_date are provided → use custom date range
2. Otherwise → use period (daily/weekly/monthly/all-time)

Returns:
- pending_transactions: {onramp: {amount, count}, offramp: {amount, count}, total: {amount, count}}
- failed_transactions: {onramp: {amount, count}, offramp: {amount, count}, total: {amount, count}}
- settled_transactions: {onramp: {amount, count}, offramp: {amount, count}, total: {amount, count}}
- unverified_transactions: {onramp: {amount, count}, offramp: {amount, count}, total: {amount, count}}
- refunded_transactions: {onramp: {amount, count}, offramp: {amount, count}, total: {amount, count}}
- total_revenue: {onramp: {amount, currency}, offramp: {amount, currency}, total: {amount, currency}}
- date_range: {start_date, end_date} (dates in EAT timezone, format: ISO 8601 with +03:00)

Defaults to weekly period if no date range is provided.
All dates are filtered using created_at (UTC) converted to EAT for business day boundaries.
